    "plan_content": "The plan is ready. Here's a summary of what I found and planned:\n\n## Plan: `Bun.INI` Namespace\n\n### What I explored\n- **`TOMLObject.zig`** and **`JSONCObject.zig`** — parse-only patterns\n- **`JSON5Object.zig`** — the parse+stringify pattern to follow for INI (both functions)\n- **`BunObject.zig`** — exact lines (66–70, 136–140, 1287–1289, 2078–2083) for lazy property registration, exports, getter functions, and imports\n- **`BunObject+exports.h`** — `FOR_EACH_GETTER` macro list (INI goes between `Glob` and `JSON5`)\n- **`BunObject.cpp`** — hash table format; INI entry goes before `JSONC` (alphabetically I < J)\n- **`bun.d.ts`** — TypeScript namespace patterns; INI block goes after `namespace JSONC` (line ~821)\n\n### 5 files to touch\n\n1. **Create** `src/bun.js/api/INIObject.zig` — self-contained INI parser (line-by-line, dotted sections, `; #` comments, `key = value`) and stringifier (`key = value` for scalars, `[section]` headers for objects), modeled after `JSON5Object.zig`\n\n2. **Modify** `src/bun.js/api/BunObject.zig` — 4 insertions: struct constant, export call, getter function, import constant\n\n3. **Modify** `src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject+exports.h` — add `macro(INI)` in alphabetical position\n\n4. **Modify** `src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject.cpp` — add INI row to hash table before JSONC\n\n5. **Modify** `packages/bun-types/bun.d.ts` — add `namespace INI` with JSDoc'd `parse` and `stringify`",
